Rating: 3
I was looking for a recipe to use leftover egg whites and found this. I'd never eaten a baked alaska, let alone made one, but this sounded fun and it was. It was really easy but you do need to plan ahead for the freezing time. I used vanilla ice cream and left out the cardamom. It's very impressive and very good. I will make it again.

Rating: 4
yummy! yummy! yummy! I had never made a baked alaska before and this was surprisingly easy. It takes time to freeze, but there is very little time spent in the kitchen. It was a hit! The peach ice cream was fabulous with the sauce! I wouldn't change a thing.

